# Backend Rules

## Stack

- Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLModel (SQLAlchemy + Pydantic), PostgreSQL
- Groq Cloud for AI (LLaMA 3.3 70B)
- httpx + feedparser for data ingestion

## Project Structure

```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py           # FastAPI app, all routes
│   ├── models.py          # SQLModel table definitions
│   ├── core/
│   │   └── database.py    # Engine, init_db, get_session
│   └── services/
│       ├── fetcher.py     # Ingestion from all sources
│       └── analyzer.py    # Classification, insights, chat
├── requirements.txt
├── compose.yaml
└── Dockerfile
```

## Conventions

- Routes live in `main.py`. Keep them thin — delegate to services.
- Database sessions via `get_session()` (FastAPI DI) or `get_script_session()` (scripts).
- Models use SQLModel with `table=True`.
- Environment: `DATABASE_URL`, `GROQ_API_KEY` (required), `GITHUB_TOKEN` (optional).

## Data Sources (fetcher.py)

Ten async hunters run in parallel via `asyncio.gather`:

| Hunter | Source | What it fetches | Default category |
|--------|--------|-----------------|------------------|
| `hunt_hn_top` | HN Firebase API | Top 35 front-page stories with scores | General (reclassified) |
| `hunt_hn_discussions` | HN Algolia API | Ask HN / Show HN with 5+ comments | Discovery / Concerns |
| `hunt_github_trending` | GitHub Search API | Multiple queries: new repos, AI repos, tools, popular LLM repos | Momentum / AI / Discovery |
| `hunt_product_launches` | Product Hunt RSS | Daily top product launches | Discovery |
| `hunt_ai_labs` | OpenAI / Anthropic / DeepMind RSS | Lab blog posts and announcements | AI |
| `hunt_infrastructure` | NVIDIA / Pinecone / Modal / Cerebras RSS | Infrastructure blog posts | AI |
| `hunt_expert_blogs` | Karpathy / SimonW / LilianWeng / Fast.ai / Altman RSS | Expert engineer posts | Momentum |
| `hunt_lobsters` | Lobsters JSON/RSS | Top technical discussions with scores | Concerns |
| `hunt_arxiv` | ArXiv API | cs.AI and cs.LG papers | Signal |
| `hunt_tech_news` | TechCrunch / TheVerge / ArsTechnica RSS | Broader AI/tech news | AI |

Quality gate: `is_gold()` filters blacklisted domains and fluff, promotes viral signals above engagement thresholds.
Per-source cap: 15 articles per ingestion run.

## Categories (analyzer.py)

| Category | Meaning | Primary sources |
|----------|---------|-----------------|
| AI | Model releases, lab news, infrastructure | AI labs, infra, tech news |
| Signal | Research breakthroughs | ArXiv |
| Momentum | Trending repos, expert builds | GitHub, expert blogs |
| Discovery | Tools, apps, frameworks to try | Product Hunt, Show HN, GitHub tools |
| Concerns | Community problems, debates | Ask HN, Reddit, Lobsters |

## Groq Usage

- Model: `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`
- Insights: 250 max tokens, temp 0.4
- Briefs: 400 max tokens, temp 0.5
- Chat: 300 max tokens, temp 0.6

## Docker

`compose.yaml`: `web` (FastAPI via gunicorn) + `db` (PostgreSQL 15, port 5433→5432)
